Launch details Starlink-23 (v1.0)

No description provided

Description: This mission launches the 23rd batch of operational Starlink satellites, which are version 1.0, from or SLC-40 or LC-39A. It is the 24th Starlink launch overall. The satellites will be delivered to low Earth orbit and will spend a few weeks maneuvering to their operational altitude. The booster is expected to land on an ASDS.
